BACKEND ARCHITECTURE AND FOLDER STRUCTURE

ROOT DIRECTORY
├── .pytest_cache/      # Auto-generated cache for testing
├── app/                # Main application source code
│   ├── _pycache_/      # Python compiled files
│   ├── api/            # API Route handlers (Endpoints)
│   ├── core/           # Configuration, security, and global constants
│   ├── database/       # Connection logic and migrations
│   ├── entities/       # Domain objects or business logic definitions
│   ├── infra/          # External service integrations (Gemini API, Lyria, etc.)
│   ├── models/         # Database schemas / ORM models (PostgreSQL)
│   └── repositories/   # Data access layer logic
├── tests/              # Unit and integration tests
├── venv/               # Python virtual environment
├── .env.example        # Template for environment variables (API Keys)
├── .gitignore          # Files to be ignored by Git
└── requirements.txt    # Project dependencies (FastAPI, GenAI, etc.)

ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW (CLEAN ARCHITECTURE APPROACH)

1. API Layer (app/api):
   - Handles HTTP requests from the Swift frontend.
   - Responsible for request validation and response formatting (JSON).

2. Infra Layer (app/infra):
   - This is where the Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite, Nano Banana 2, and Lyria 3 
     integrations live. 
   - Handles communication with Google Cloud/Vertex AI.

3. Models & Database (app/models & app/database):
   - Defines the PostgreSQL structure.
   - Manages persistence for user creative sessions or history.

4. Core (app/core):
   - Stores the logic for loading the .env file and configuring 
     the Global Generative AI settings.
